cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on action recognition in videos using visual attributes extracted from individual frames. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a multi-stream 3D CNN framework, which involves deep learning techniques such as object detection, encoding, and classification, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of visual attributes suggests a potential application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper involves classification tasks, which could also fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
